                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "B4DlV",
                  "fill": "$foreground-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "An exploration of how clean architecture principles help build maintainable, testable software systems that stand the test of time.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "GbA7f",
                  "fill": "$border-subtle",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 1
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "hE9Kj",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Software architecture is the foundation upon which all code is built. Without a clear architectural vision, projects inevitably devolve into tangled dependency graphs that resist change and breed bugs.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "pBVVE",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The Dependency Rule",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 22,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "oSDgk",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The fundamental rule is simple: source code dependencies must point inward. Nothing in an inner circle can know anything about something in an outer circle.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "2gxLb",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Practical Implementation in .NET",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 22,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "yshJ3",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "In a .NET solution, this manifests as separate projects: Domain, Application, Infrastructure, and API. MediatR serves as the messaging backbone.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
